# Example cron job configuration for auto eligibility checker
# Run every minute

# ============================================================================
# HOW TO RUN FROM CLI (MANUAL EXECUTION)
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Navigate to the service directory:
#    cd /path/to/services/auto-eligibility-checker
#
# 2. Activate virtual environment (if using one):
#    source venv/bin/activate
#    # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
#
# 3. Run the script:
#    python main.py
#    # OR if using python3 explicitly:
#    python3 main.py
#
# 4. The script will:
#    - Fetch today's appointments
#    - Process new appointments
#    - Create eligibility checks
#    - Display metrics and exit
#
# Prerequisites:
# - Python 3.8+ installed
# - Virtual environment created and dependencies installed (pip install -r requirements.txt)
# - .env file configured with required variables (REDIS_URL, API_BASE_URL, etc.)
#
# ============================================================================
# SETTING UP CRON JOB (AUTOMATED EXECUTION)
# ============================================================================
#
# To install, run: crontab -e
# Then add this line (adjust paths as needed):
#
# * * * * * cd /path/to/services/auto-eligibility-checker && /path/to/venv/bin/python main.py >> /var/log/eligibility-checker.log 2>&1
#
# Make sure to:
# 1. Update the paths to match your installation
# 2. Ensure the .env file is in the service directory
# 3. Set proper permissions on the log file directory
# 4. Test the script manually before adding to cron (use CLI instructions above)

